# Run & Rhythm: Strava + Spotify Integration Architecture

This document outlines the architecture, roadmap, and technical details for building a full-stack application that correlates Strava runs with Spotify listening history.

## 1. System Architecture

The application will use a modern React frontend, a FastAPI backend, and a PostgreSQL (or SQLite) database to manage users, tokens, and run/playlist data.

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant User
    participant Frontend
    participant Backend
    participant Strava API
    participant Spotify API
    participant Database

    User->>Frontend: Login with Strava & Spotify
    Frontend->>Backend: Initiate OAuth Flow
    Backend->>Strava API: Request Strava Access
    Backend->>Spotify API: Request Spotify Access
    Backend->>Database: Store User OAuth Tokens
    
    User->>Frontend: View Recent Runs
    Frontend->>Backend: Get Runs
    Backend->>Strava API: Fetch Recent Activities
    Backend->>Spotify API: Fetch Recently Played Tracks
    Backend->>Backend: Match Tracks to Run Timestamps
    Backend->>Database: Store Processed Run & Tracks
    Backend-->>Frontend: Return Run + Playlist Data
    Frontend-->>User: Display Statistics & Songs
```

### Components
- **Frontend (React)**: Handles user authentication UI, displays run statistics, and lists matched songs.
- **Backend (FastAPI)**: Manages OAuth 2.0 flows, communicates with external APIs, processes data (timestamp matching), and exposes REST endpoints for the frontend.
- **Database (SQLite/PostgreSQL)**: Stores user details, OAuth access/refresh tokens securely, cached run data, and matched playlists to avoid re-fetching.

